    java.io.Serializable

    public class CareProviderRecord
extends Record
    A basic extension of the Record object that simply attributes the record to a specified CareProvider object by that care provider's uuid.

      • setCare_provider

        public void setCare_provider(java.lang.String assigned_care_provider)
                      throws ReassignmentException
        Sets the care provider that this CareProviderRecord is associated with.

        Each CareProviderRecord can only be associated with one CareProvider object ever. Therefore, if someone attempts to reassign this record to another care provider then this method will fail and throw a ReassignmentException.

        Parameters:
        assigned_care_provider - String type uuid that represents the unique identifier of the CareProvider object that this CareProviderRecord object is associated with.
        Throws:
        ReassignmentException - Warns that this record has already been attributed to a care provider and should not be reassigned.
